summary: The third game of State of Origin, an annual rugby league rivalry between New South Wales (NSW) and Queensland (QLD), was held at Suncorp Stadium in Brisbane. Despite QLD's impressive recent record at the stadium, NSW emerged victorious, winning the series. The crowd at Suncorp Stadium was announced, and the NSW Blues defeated the Queensland Maroons. Despite not being selected for the game, an NSW Blues player was surprisingly sent to the sheds, causing confusion. Game 3 also marked the 30th anniversary of Suncorp Stadium and saw the announcement of plans for a supercomputer the size of the stadium near the airport.
